# Cursor Rules for Pyro Project

## MCP Server Configuration

The MCP Translator Server is available for translating source code to Cryptex structure.

To use it in Cursor:
1. Add to your Cursor MCP settings (Settings > Features > MCP)
2. Or use the configuration in `mcp-translator/mcp-config.json`

## Project Structure

- `pyro-core/` - Main Pyro application
- `cryptex/` - Hierarchical file structure system
- `fire-marshal/` - Data flow orchestration
- `node-red-bridge/` - Node-RED integration
- `mcp-translator/` - MCP server for code translation

## Anarchist Branding

- Use Pyro/Fire Marshal themed naming
- Apply anarchist principles to code organization
- Maintain autonomous, decentralized architecture

